5000|$|In the United States, BRT {{began in}} 1977, with Pittsburgh's South <b>Busway,</b> {{operating}} on 4.3 mi of exclusive lanes. Its success {{led to the}} Martin Luther King Jr. East <b>Busway</b> in 1983, a fuller BRT deployment including a dedicated <b>busway</b> of , traffic signal preemption, and peak service headway as low as two minutes. After {{the opening of the}} West <b>Busway,</b> [...] in length in 1990, Pittsburgh’s <b>Busway</b> system is today over 18.5 miles long.|$|R
